      <hedline>
        <hl1>New Twists on the Mideast Road</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Judy Lash Balint letter disputes July 30 Week in Review article on failure of Camp David summit</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Nothing Succeeds Like a Failure'' (Week in Review, July 30):</p>
        <p>You try to put a positive spin on the failure of the Camp David talks by citing Israeli commentators who note the sea change in Israeli attitudes regarding hot-button issues.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Nothing Succeeds Like a Failure'' (Week in Review, July 30):</p>
        <p>You try to put a positive spin on the failure of the Camp David talks by citing Israeli commentators who note the sea change in Israeli attitudes regarding hot-button issues.</p>
        <p>It's been seven years since the Israelis and the Palestinians agreed to suspend incitement and educate toward compromise and peace. In this time the Palestinian Authority has chosen to disregard its commitment and continues to educate its youth in the ways of violence and hatred. Israelis who have made a painful 180-degree turn to achieve peace can have no cause for optimism as long as the Palestinians haven't done the same.</p>
        <p>JUDY LASH BALINT  Jerusalem, July 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
